# Model Routing: {{.ProjectName}}

## Strategy

This project uses different AI models for different types of tasks. Each task is assigned to the most appropriate model.

## Model Assignments
{{if .Agents.Enabled}}
| Responsibility | Model |
|---|---|
| Hard architecture decisions | {{.Agents.DefaultModelStrategy.ReasoningHeavy}} |
| Heavy/complex coding | {{.Agents.DefaultModelStrategy.ComplexCoding}} |
| Medium complexity coding | {{.Agents.DefaultModelStrategy.MediumCoding}} |
| Frontend and simple tasks | {{.Agents.DefaultModelStrategy.FrontendLowMedium}} |
| File operations and mechanical tasks | {{.Agents.DefaultModelStrategy.FileOps}} |
{{else}}
Model routing not configured. Define in project.kernel.yaml > agents section.
{{end}}
## Task-to-Model Mapping

| Task Type | Model | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| Architecture Design | reasoning-heavy | ADR creation, system design |
| Core Backend Logic | complex-coding | Business rules, API implementation |
| Middleware/Integration | medium-coding | Auth middleware, service integration |
| UI Components | frontend-low-medium | React components, styling |
| Scaffolding/Refactors | file-ops | File creation, renames, simple changes |

## Usage

When creating a task, use:

```bash
archseed agent generate --model <model> --title "task description"
```
